WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.125
The 2024 ACC Expert Consensus

00:00:03.125 --> 00:00:06.250
Decision Pathway identifies five key

00:00:06.250 --> 00:00:07.500
high-risk features.

00:00:07.500 --> 00:00:10.625
First: hemodynamic instability or cardiogenic

00:00:10.625 --> 00:00:12.500
shock on presentation.

00:00:12.500 --> 00:00:15.625
Second: biventricular dysfunction on echocardiography.

00:00:15.625 --> 00:00:18.750
Third: late gadolinium enhancement on

00:00:18.750 --> 00:00:21.875
cardiac MRI, indicating irreversible fibrosis.

00:00:21.875 --> 00:00:25.000
Fourth: endomyocardial biopsy confirming giant

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:27.500
cell or eosinophilic histology.

00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:30.625
Fifth: sustained ventricular arrhythmias or

00:00:30.625 --> 00:00:32.500
advanced AV block.

00:00:32.500 --> 00:00:35.625
These criteria should trigger urgent

00:00:35.625 --> 00:00:38.750
referral, endomyocardial biopsy, and consideration

00:00:38.750 --> 00:00:40.000
of immunosuppression.
